article.headline: San Diego St. 59, UC Riverside 46
article.story: SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Kelvin Davis scored 16 points and Lorrenzo Wade added 14 to lead San Diego State to a 59-46 win over UC Riverside on Tuesday night. Davis hit 6-of-12 shots on a night when San Diego State (8-1) made only 34 percent of its field goal attempts, including a 3-of-15 shooting performance from 3-point range. The win matched the best nine-game start in San Diego State's 38-year Division I history. It was the fifth time the Aztecs have reached the mark, including last season. San Diego State has beaten UC Riverside (2-6) in all seven meetings. Larry Cunningham scored a game-high 21 points for the Highlanders, who committed 22 turnovers and were outrebounded 38-30. Richie Williams added 13 points for San Diego State, which made 20 of 25 free throws compared to UC Riverside's 7-for-11.
